Spinnaker authenticates with the primary role and assumes itself for primary role.

This needs two things:
a) Permissions to DO things
b) Trust to allow "assume" role from the primary account

==========================================================================
PERMISSIONS (policy)
==========================================================================
See sample-target-policy



==================================================================
TRUST RELATIONSHIP: If coming from EKS, trust "role" srini-nonroot-role and
set up the worker nodes with with role. 
For non-EKS, trust "user" srini-nonroot instead of the role
==================================================================
{
  "Version": "2008-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Principal": {
        "AWS": "arn:aws:iam::<account1>:role/srini-nonroot"
      },
      "Action": "sts:AssumeRole"
    }
  ]
}
